# Master store list for the dashboard.
# Copy this file to `.storelist` and edit it. The `.storelist` file is the single
# source of truth: it controls WHICH stores are scraped/served AND their trading hours.
# Add a line to add a store; remove a line to drop it.
#
# Format (pipe-delimited):
#   store# | name | openHour | closeHour | area | timeZone
#   store# | name | area | timeZone                     (for per-day schedules)
#   store# | name                                        (defaults: Area 22 + dashboard TZ)
#   - openHour  = first trading hour shown (24h clock)
#   - closeHour = closing hour (24h clock); the last column shown is closeHour - 1
#   - area      = used to group stores in the picker and area dashboards (e.g. Area 22)
#   - timeZone  = IANA name (e.g. Australia/Melbourne, Australia/Perth)
#   - midnight close may be written as 24 or 0; hours past midnight as 25, 26 (1AM = 25)
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Different hours on different days:
#   Leave the hours off the store line, then add one line per weekday beneath it.
#   Day names: Monday..Sunday (or Mon/Tue/Wed/Thu/Fri/Sat/Sun). Indenting is optional.
#   Any weekday you don't list falls back to the store's plain line (if it has hours)
#   or the 10-22 default. Hours are resolved for "today" in Australia/Melbourne.
#
# Examples — same hours every day:
3806 | Dandenong South | 10 | 23 | Area 22 | Australia/Melbourne
3808 | Berwick South   | 10 | 23 | Area 22 | Australia/Melbourne
3811 | Chirnside Park  | 10 | 22 | Area 22 | Australia/Melbourne
3902 | Ellenbrook North | 10 | 22 | Area 22 | Australia/Perth
3903 | Canning Vale     | 10 | 23 | Area 22 | Australia/Perth
3904 | Butler           | 10 | 22 | Area 22 | Australia/Perth
#
# Example — per-day hours (open 10 daily, late on Fri/Sat):
3901 | Midland | Area 22 | Australia/Perth
    Monday    | 10 | 23
    Tuesday   | 10 | 23
    Wednesday | 10 | 23
    Thursday  | 10 | 23
    Friday    | 10 | 24
    Saturday  | 10 | 24
    Sunday    | 10 | 23
